CHART NAME: kafka
CHART VERSION: 29.3.13
APP VERSION: 3.7.1

** Please be patient while the chart is being deployed **

Kafka can be accessed by consumers via port 9092 on the following DNS name from within your cluster:

    kafka.reportnet.svc.cluster.local

Each Kafka broker can be accessed by producers via port 9092 on the following DNS name(s) from within your cluster:

    kafka-controller-0.kafka-controller-headless.reportnet.svc.cluster.local:9092
    kafka-controller-1.kafka-controller-headless.reportnet.svc.cluster.local:9092
    kafka-controller-2.kafka-controller-headless.reportnet.svc.cluster.local:9092

To create a pod that you can use as a Kafka client run the following commands:

    kubectl run kafka-client --restart='Never' --image docker.io/bitnamilegacy/kafka:3.7.1-debian-12-r4 --namespace reportnet --command -- sleep infinity
    kubectl exec --tty -i kafka-client --namespace reportnet -- bash

    PRODUCER:
        kafka-console-producer.sh \
            --broker-list kafka-controller-0.kafka-controller-headless.reportnet.svc.cluster.local:9092,kafka-controller-1.kafka-controller-headless.reportnet.svc.cluster.local:9092,kafka-controller-2.kafka-controller-headless.reportnet.svc.cluster.local:9092 \
            --topic test

    CONSUMER:
        kafka-console-consumer.sh \
            --bootstrap-server kafka.reportnet.svc.cluster.local:9092 \
            --topic test \
            --from-beginning

